metadata.name: M81 and M82
metadata.description:
M81 and M82 are 2 galaxies located near the Big Dipper.  M81 (upper right) is called the Bodes Nebula.  M82 (lower left) is called the Cigar Galaxy.  This image is HaRGB, meaning I combined regular broadband colors with hydrogen alpha (narrowband) data. The red/pink regions are where nebulae are in the galaxies and where new stars and planets might be forming.  Both are about 12 million light years from Earth. 

This is my 1 year in NFTs anniversary edition!
